TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the NRE_CLM_CD != 0, then the claim is non-rebate eligible and we need to count it. If that is TRUE, then check to see if there's only a single exception code on the claim. If THAT is also TRUE, then use the Single_Excpt_Cnt value (should be 1) for this count field.

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the NRE_CLM_CD != 0, then the claim is non-rebate eligible and we need to count it. If that is TRUE, then check to see if there are MULTIPLE exception codes on the claim. If THAT is also TRUE, then use the Mult_Excpt_Cnt value for this count field.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: MULT_EXCPT_QTY

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the NRE_CLM_CD != 0, then the claim is non-rebate eligible and we need to count it. If that is TRUE, then check to see if there are MULTIPLE exception codes on the claim. If THAT is also TRUE, then use the Mult_Excpt_Cnt value for this count field.

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, then these the CLM_GID_Excpt_logic field, coming from the Exception logic in the mapping, would be NULL, and we need to count this claim since all other counters hold exception counts.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: RBEL_CLM_CNT_QTY

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, then these the CLM_GID_Excpt_logic field, coming from the Exception logic in the mapping, would be NULL, and we need to count this claim since all other counters hold exception counts.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: sum_RBEL_CLM_CNT_QTY

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, then these the CLM_GID_Excpt_logic field, coming from the Exception logic in the mapping, would be NULL, and we need to count this claim since all other counters hold exception counts. test
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: NRE_CLNT_CNT_QTY

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, then these the CLM_GID_Excpt_logic field, coming from the Exception logic in the mapping, would be NULL, and we need to count this claim since all other counters hold exception counts. test

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This expression will determine where this claims falls - single exception counts or multiple exception counts.

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the input Clm_Excpt_Cnt = 1, then there is only a single exception on this claim - the Single_Excpt_Cnt needs to be incremented by 1.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: Single_Excpt_Cnt

TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: sum_NRE_CLNT_CNT_QTY

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This expression will guide the counts to the RE claim count, NRE claim count, Single, and Multiple exception claim counts.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: exp_Set_Rebate_Elig_Clm_Cnt_Value

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: The CLM_GID from the Exception logic in the mapping.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: CLM_GID_Excpt_logic

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, then these the CLM_GID_Excpt_logic field, coming from the Exception logic in the mapping, would be NULL, and we need to count this claim since all other counters hold exception counts. test
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF((NRE_CLM_CD='0' AND RBEL_CLNT_CD='1'),1 -- The claim is Rebate Eligible, The client is rebate eligible ,0) -- One or more of the exceptions on the claim cause the claim to be NRE_CLM_CD value 1 or 2 or the client is non rebate eligible
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION_DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, then these the CLM_GID_Excpt_logic field, coming from the Exception logic in the mapping, would be NULL, and we need to count this claim since all other counters hold exception counts.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: RBEL_CLM_CNT_QTY

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, that does not make a claim Rebate Eligible. The client must also be Rebate Eligible. If there are no exceptions and the claims client is NRE, then this count needs to reflect that.
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF((NRE_CLM_CD='0' AND RBEL_CLNT_CD = '0'),1 -- The claim is Rebate Eligible BUT the client is NRE ,0) -- One or more of the exceptions on the claim cause the claim to be NRE_CLM_CD value 1 or 2
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION_DESCRIPTION: If there are no exceptions for a CLM_GID, then these the CLM_GID_Excpt_logic field, coming from the Exception logic in the mapping, would be NULL, and we need to count this claim since all other counters hold exception counts.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: NRE_CLNT_CNT_QTY

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the NRE_CLM_CD != 0, then the claim is non-rebate eligible and we need to count it. If that is TRUE, then check to see if there's only a single exception code on the claim. If THAT is also TRUE, then we increment the Single_Excpt_Cnt value by 1.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: SNGL_EXCPT_QTY

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the NRE_CLM_CD != 0, then the claim is non-rebate eligible and we need to count it. If that is TRUE, then check to see if there are MULTIPLE exception codes on the claim. If THAT is also TRUE, then we increment the Mult_Excpt_Cnt value by 1.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: MULT_EXCPT_QTY
